---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How It Works | Thornveil"
  description="How RigRun, Pyros, Mycelium, and the Agent Factory deliver local-first AI — unlimited inference on your hardware, a standalone safety perimeter for any LLM, self-healing distributed mesh, and custom agents built in days."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="section-padding pt-32 md:pt-40">
    <div class="container-max mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.3em] uppercase reveal" style="color: var(--color-accent);">How it works</p>
      <h1 class="text-fluid-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight mt-3 reveal reveal-delay-1">What you get under the hood</h1>
      <p class="text-base mt-4 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed reveal reveal-delay-2" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
        Four systems that turn a single GPU (or a room full of laptops) into a private AI stack your team controls end-to-end. No cloud, no per-token billing, no data leaving your building.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RIGRUN -->
  <section class="section-padding pt-12" style="background: var(--color-surface-secondary);">
    <div class="container-max mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-12 lg:gap-16">
        <div class="lg:col-span-3">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 reveal">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center" style="background: var(--color-accent-muted); color: var(--color-accent); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9.813 15.904L9 18.75l-.813-2.846a4.5 4.5 0 00-3.09-3.09L2.25 12l2.846-.813a4.5 4.5 0 003.09-3.09L9 5.25l.813 2.846a4.5 4.5 0 003.09 3.09L15.75 12l-2.846.813a4.5 4.5 0 00-3.09 3.09z" /></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-fluid-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">RigRun</h2>
              <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">Unlimited inference on your hardware</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed reveal reveal-delay-1" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            <p>A frontier-class model running in your server room, priced like electricity instead of tokens. One GPU, one binary, unlimited queries. Your sensitive code and documents never leave your network.</p>
            <p>RigRun ships with everything your team needs on day one: a safety stack that blocks adversarial prompts, a fast-and-slow dual-model cascade that keeps latency down, and an overnight self-improvement loop so the model gets better on your workload without ever going offline.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-8 space-y-3 reveal reveal-delay-2">
            {[
              { label: 'Fit more context into the same GPU', detail: "TurboQuant compresses the KV cache 5.2× (paper submitted, under review) so you get longer conversations and larger codebases in memory without buying a second GPU. Combined with Rolling Memory v4, effective context becomes unlimited." },
              { label: 'Model learns your workflow overnight', detail: 'ZO2 training pipeline improves the model from your real usage while inference keeps serving. Wake up to a model that knows your codebase better than yesterday. Zero downtime.' },
              { label: 'Safety stack you can defend in an audit', detail: 'Five layers — action gating, learned classifier, trajectory anomaly detection, declarative policy DSL, and classification spillage detection — stop prompt-injection and data exfiltration before they reach the model.' },
              { label: 'Fast by default, deep when it matters', detail: 'Cascade routes between the 122B MoE fast-path (17B active parameters at 184 tok/s) and full expert activation (105 tok/s). Single model, dual speed. Your users get answers fast; full expert depth engages only when it matters.' },
            ].map((item) => (
              <div class="rounded-lg p-4" style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);">
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">{item.label}</div>
                <div class="text-xs leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">{item.detail}</div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lg:col-span-2 reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="rounded-xl p-6" style="background: var(--color-surface-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
            <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-wider uppercase mb-5" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">Specs</h3>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              {[
                { label: 'Model', value: 'Qwen3.5-122B-A10B' },
                { label: 'Parameters', value: '397B total / 17B active (MoE)' },
                { label: 'Generation', value: '105 tok/s (122B)' },
                { label: 'Fast mode', value: '184 tok/s (35B)' },
                { label: 'Context', value: '1M tokens (YaRN)' },
                { label: 'Effective context', value: 'Unlimited (Rolling Memory)' },
                { label: 'KV Compression', value: '5.2x (TurboQuant)' },
                { label: 'VRAM', value: '96GB (98% utilized)' },
                { label: 'Hardware', value: 'RTX PRO 6000 Blackwell' },
                { label: 'Per-token fee', value: '$0 — ever' },
                { label: 'Data egress', value: 'None (fully on-prem)' },
{ label: 'Architecture', value: 'Model-agnostic. Any GGUF, GPTQ, or AWQ model is hot-swappable.' },
              ].map((s) => (
                <div class="flex justify-between items-baseline">
                  <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">{s.label}</span>
                  <span class="font-mono text-xs font-medium">{s.value}</span>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PYROS -->
  <section class="section-padding">
    <div class="container-max mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-12 lg:gap-16">
        <div class="lg:col-span-3">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 reveal">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center" style="background: var(--color-accent-muted); color: var(--color-accent); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12c0 1.268-.63 2.39-1.593 3.068a3.745 3.745 0 01-1.043 3.296 3.745 3.745 0 01-3.296 1.043A3.745 3.745 0 0112 21c-1.268 0-2.39-.63-3.068-1.593a3.746 3.746 0 01-3.296-1.043 3.745 3.745 0 01-1.043-3.296A3.745 3.745 0 013 12c0-1.268.63-2.39 1.593-3.068a3.745 3.745 0 011.043-3.296 3.746 3.746 0 013.296-1.043A3.746 3.746 0 0112 3c1.268 0 2.39.63 3.068 1.593a3.746 3.746 0 013.296 1.043 3.746 3.746 0 011.043 3.296A3.745 3.745 0 0121 12z" /></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-fluid-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Pyros</h2>
              <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">A safety perimeter for any LLM</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed reveal reveal-delay-1" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            <p>A 17,000-line pure-Go engine that wraps any large language model in a 7-pillar safety pipeline. Most LLM safety stacks are Python wrappers around a moderation API call. Pyros is a separate process that implements the actual algorithms from the literature — SmoothLLM, isotonic calibration, EvoPrompt, negative-selection AIS, PID homeostasis — instead of forwarding the question to a hosted classifier.</p>
            <p>Pyros doesn't require RigRun. Drop it in front of OpenAI, Anthropic, vLLM, llama.cpp, Ollama, or anything else that speaks the OpenAI-compatible chat completions format.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-8 space-y-3 reveal reveal-delay-2">
            {[
              { label: 'Real prompt-injection blocking, not vibes', detail: 'Multi-signal injection scanner blocks at confidence ≥ 0.7 before the request reaches the model. SmoothLLM perturbation + supermajority vote layered on top. Negative-selection AIS detectors learn what your traffic normally looks like and flag what does not.' },
              { label: 'Hallucination probe with measured weights', detail: '6 weighted features: 4-gram repetition (0.25), entity consistency (0.20), numeric density (0.10), hedge density (-0.15), entropy variance (0.25), confidence gap (0.20). Negative hedge weight is intentional — hedging is a signal of calibration, not failure.' },
              { label: 'Pure Go, ships as one binary', detail: 'Reimplements PAVA isotonic regression, UCB1 contextual bandit, cosine vector store, discrete-event simulator, MDL compressor, and EvoPrompt crossover from primary sources. No Python runtime, no CGO, no transitive C library surface. Drops onto an air-gapped system without an installer.' },
              { label: 'Hardened in production', detail: 'Constant-time bearer auth (subtle.ConstantTimeCompare), admission semaphore, in-flight WaitGroup tracked, async PostWorker drained before persistence, HMAC-chained audit log, Prometheus metrics. Fuzz tests across the safety surface, race tests across all 28 packages.' },
            ].map((item) => (
              <div class="rounded-lg p-4" style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);">
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">{item.label}</div>
                <div class="text-xs leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">{item.detail}</div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lg:col-span-2 reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="rounded-xl p-6" style="background: var(--color-surface-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
            <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-wider uppercase mb-5" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">The 7 Pillars</h3>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              {[
                { num: 'I', name: 'Oracle', role: 'Predictive intel' },
                { num: 'II', name: 'Tribunal', role: 'Adversarial verification' },
                { num: 'III', name: 'Fortress', role: 'Pre-inference defense' },
                { num: 'IV', name: 'MindEye', role: 'Metacognition' },
                { num: 'V', name: 'Forge', role: 'Self-improvement' },
                { num: 'VI', name: 'Crucible', role: 'Operational safety' },
                { num: 'VII', name: 'Singularity', role: 'Homeostatic regulation' },
              ].map((p) => (
                <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 text-xs">
                  <span class="font-mono font-bold w-4" style="color: var(--color-accent);">{p.num}</span>
                  <span class="font-semibold">{p.name}</span>
                  <span class="font-mono flex-1 text-right" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">{p.role}</span>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
            <div class="mt-5 pt-4" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);">
              <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-center">
                <div>
                  <div class="font-mono text-base font-bold" style="color: var(--color-accent);">17K</div>
                  <div class="font-mono text-[9px] tracking-wider uppercase mt-1" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">LOC pure Go</div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <div class="font-mono text-base font-bold" style="color: var(--color-accent);">0</div>
                  <div class="font-mono text-[9px] tracking-wider uppercase mt-1" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">Python deps</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MYCELIUM -->
  <section class="section-padding" style="background: var(--color-surface-secondary);">
    <div class="container-max mx-auto">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-12 lg:gap-16">
        <div class="lg:col-span-2 reveal reveal-delay-1 order-2 lg:order-1">
          <div class="rounded-xl p-6" style="background: var(--color-surface-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
            <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-wider uppercase mb-5" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">Device Tiers</h3>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              {[
                { tier: 'Phone', model: '0.6-1.7B', ram: '4-8GB', speed: '15-30 tok/s' },
                { tier: 'Laptop', model: '4-30B', ram: '8-32GB', speed: '10-40 tok/s' },
                { tier: 'Workstation', model: '30-72B', ram: '24-48GB', speed: '20-50 tok/s' },
                { tier: 'Server', model: '122B+', ram: '96GB+', speed: '105+ tok/s' },
                { tier: 'Cluster', model: '400B+ distributed', ram: 'Pooled', speed: 'Variable' },
              ].map((t) => (
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-xs">
                  <span class="font-semibold w-20">{t.tier}</span>
                  <span class="font-mono flex-1" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">{t.model}</span>
                  <span class="font-mono" style="color: var(--color-accent);">{t.speed}</span>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lg:col-span-3 order-1 lg:order-2">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 reveal">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center" style="background: var(--color-accent-muted); color: var(--color-accent); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M7.5 21L3 16.5m0 0L7.5 12M3 16.5h13.5m0-13.5L21 7.5m0 0L16.5 12M21 7.5H7.5" /></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-fluid-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Mycelium</h2>
              <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">Scale out without a data center</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed reveal reveal-delay-1" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            <p>Turn any collection of devices — phones, laptops, vehicles, servers — into a single AI cluster that heals itself. Need more capacity? Plug in another node. Lose a node in the field? The mesh routes around it. Works offline, survives network partitions, and has no single point of failure to defend.</p>
            <p>Mycelium runs over the network you already have. No InfiniBand. No specialized hardware. No data center buildout.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-8 space-y-3 reveal reveal-delay-2">
            {[
              { label: 'Works over the WiFi you already have', detail: 'Inference distributes across devices by routing only the small subset of MoE experts each token actually needs. No InfiniBand, no specialized interconnects, no datacenter-grade switches required.' },
              { label: 'Trust nodes you do not own', detail: 'Every node proves it actually ran the work — through behavioral spot checks, signed execution traces, and reputation scoring. A compromised or lazy node gets caught and kicked out. No trusted hardware chips required.' },
              { label: 'One consistent voice across devices', detail: 'A query that lands on a phone and one that lands on your server return answers in the same style and format. Your users never know (or care) which device answered.' },
              { label: 'Classification stays put', detail: 'UNCLASSIFIED routes anywhere. CUI stays on your mesh. SECRET never leaves the device it originated on. Enforced at the routing layer — not as an afterthought.' },
            ].map((item) => (
              <div class="rounded-lg p-4" style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);">
                <div class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">{item.label}</div>
                <div class="text-xs leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">{item.detail}</div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- AGENT FACTORY -->
  <section class="section-padding" style="background: var(--color-surface-secondary);">
    <div class="container-max mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 reveal">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center" style="background: var(--color-accent-muted); color: var(--color-accent); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M11.42 15.17l-5.1-5.1m0 0L11.42 4.97m-5.1 5.1H20.4" /></svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-fluid-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Agent Factory</h2>
          <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">Custom AI agents in days, not months</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed reveal reveal-delay-1" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
        <p>Tell us what you need your AI to do, in plain English. You get back a production-ready agent — with the right tools, the right knowledge base, the right guardrails, and an evaluation rubric your team can audit. Every agent goes through adversarial stress tests and a human approval gate before it ever touches your users.</p>
        <p>The result: a bespoke AI specialist tuned to your workflow, delivered in days instead of months of prompt engineering. And every agent keeps getting better from real usage.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <a href="/products" class="btn-primary text-sm">
          See the agents &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="divider my-12 reveal reveal-delay-3"></div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-8 text-center reveal reveal-delay-3">
        <div>
          <div class="stat-number text-fluid-xl" style="color: var(--color-accent);">14</div>
          <div class="text-xs mt-1" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">Pipeline<br/>steps</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="stat-number text-fluid-xl" style="color: var(--color-accent);">12</div>
          <div class="text-xs mt-1" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">Tools in<br/>registry</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="stat-number text-fluid-xl" style="color: var(--color-accent);">5</div>
          <div class="text-xs mt-1" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">Adversarial<br/>probes</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COMPLIANCE -->
  <section class="section-padding" style="background: var(--color-surface-secondary);">
    <div class="container-max mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-14 text-center">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.3em] uppercase reveal" style="color: var(--color-accent);">
          Compliance
        </p>
        <h2 class="text-fluid-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mt-3 reveal reveal-delay-1">
          Security & Compliance
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm mt-4 max-w-xl mx-auto leading-relaxed reveal reveal-delay-2" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
          Controls implemented. Certification in progress.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <!-- Implemented Controls -->
        <div class="card-gradient-border p-7 reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <div class="relative z-10">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center" style="background: var(--color-accent-muted); color: var(--color-accent); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75m-3-7.036A11.959 11.959 0 013.598 6 11.99 11.99 0 003 9.749c0 5.592 3.824 10.29 9 11.623 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.31-.21-2.571-.598-3.751h-.152c-3.196 0-6.1-1.248-8.25-3.285z" /></svg>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight">Implemented Controls</h3>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-5">
              <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-wider uppercase mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">NIST 800-53 Rev 5</h4>
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-2">
                {[
                  'AC-2 Account Management',
                  'AC-4 Information Flow',
                  'AU-2 Audit Events',
                  'AU-9 Audit Protection',
                  'IA-2 Multi-Factor Auth',
                  'IA-5 Authenticator Mgmt',
                  'IR-4 Incident Handling',
                  'SC-8 Transmission Confidentiality',
                  'SC-13 Cryptographic Protection',
                  'SC-28 Data at Rest',
                  'PS-6 Access Agreements',
                ].map((ctrl) => (
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
                    <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full flex-shrink-0" style="background: var(--color-accent);"></span>
                    {ctrl}
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-2 mt-5">
              {[
                'Classification enforcement (UNCLASS through TS)',
                'AES-256-GCM encryption at rest with PBKDF2 key derivation',
                'HMAC-chained audit logs with tamper detection',
                'JWT/OAuth/OIDC authentication with MFA (TOTP)',
              ].map((item) => (
                <div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
                  <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 mt-1" style="background: var(--color-accent);"></span>
                  {item}
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Certification Roadmap -->
        <div class="card-gradient-border p-7 reveal reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="relative z-10">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center" style="background: var(--color-accent-muted); color: var(--color-accent); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
                <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 6.75V15m6-6v8.25m.503 3.498l4.875-2.437c.381-.19.622-.58.622-1.006V4.82c0-.836-.88-1.38-1.628-1.006l-3.869 1.934c-.317.159-.69.159-1.006 0L9.503 3.252a1.125 1.125 0 00-1.006 0L3.622 5.689C3.24 5.88 3 6.27 3 6.695V19.18c0 .836.88 1.38 1.628 1.006l3.869-1.934c.317-.159.69-.159 1.006 0l4.994 2.497c.317.158.69.158 1.006 0z" /></svg>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight">Certification Roadmap</h3>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-4">
              {[
                { cert: 'SOC 2 Type II', status: 'In planning', color: '#f97316' },
                { cert: 'CMMC Level 2', status: 'Controls implemented, assessment pending', color: '#3b82f6' },
                { cert: 'FedRAMP', status: 'Not yet pursued (requires sponsoring agency)', color: '#6b7280' },
                { cert: 'ATO', status: 'SSP in development, pen test pending', color: '#f97316' },
                { cert: 'FIPS 140-3', status: 'Runtime verification implemented, formal validation pending', color: '#3b82f6' },
              ].map((item) => (
                <div class="rounded-lg p-4" style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);">
                  <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-1">
                    <span class="text-sm font-semibold">{item.cert}</span>
                    <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full" style={`background: ${item.color};`}></span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">{item.status}</div>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>

            <div class="mt-6 rounded-lg p-4" style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle); background: var(--color-surface-elevated);">
              <p class="text-xs leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-text-tertiary);">
                Thornveil is transparent about what is implemented and what is in progress. No certification is claimed until formally granted.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  import Lenis from 'lenis';
  const lenis = new Lenis({ duration: 1.2, easing: (t: number) => Math.min(1, 1.001 - Math.pow(2, -10 * t)) });
  function raf(time: number) { lenis.raf(time); requestAnimationFrame(raf); }
  requestAnimationFrame(raf);
</script>
